The code for a border crossing is placed after the location name, for
example "Harwich >< "

Country codes are placed after the location name:
&#039;Oxford (GB)&#039;.

The mail option of the program is only enabled when running under 
Windows 95 or Windows NT

The CD-ROM contains a copy of the manual in the file called MANUAL.PDF.
This manual is stored in the PDF-format.
The contents of the file can be viewed and printed with the Acrobat(r) vieuwer
or with your default web browser. You are offered the possibility to install
the software needed when you install Route Planner Europe.
The Acrobat software can be installed seperatly. The directory ACROBAT contains
two sub-directories. When using Windows 3.1 start the application SETUP.EXE in
the directory "16bit", else start the application SETUP.EXE in the directory
"32bit".

We wish you a safe and pleasant journey

Sony Route Planner
